1. inifinity exists in numpy
2. There are two types of error
    a. compile time error(error occurred while compiling the code.)
    b. run time error(error occurred while running the code.)

example Flight Crash because of not handling an exception.

3. try except in python doesn't handle the compile time error.
    it only handles the run time Error.

4. try, except, else, finally are the four blocks available for exception handling.
5. raise Exception("your description of Exception")